---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Vampire Crawlers Endless Mode Guide — Tips, Strategy & Best Builds (2026)';
const description = 'Master Vampire Crawlers Endless Mode. Best builds for high floors, scaling strategies, relic priorities, and how to survive past Floor 50.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical="https://vampcrawlers.cc/guides/endless-mode">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2">Vampire Crawlers Endless Mode Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">How to push deep into Endless Mode. Strategy, build recommendations, and scaling tips.</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">What Is Endless Mode?</h2>
        <p>Endless Mode unlocks after beating Floor 30 (The First Vampire). Floors continue indefinitely with progressive difficulty scaling. Every 5 floors after Floor 30, enemy HP and damage increase by 15%.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Best Build for Endless Mode</h2>
        <p>The <strong>Blood DPS build</strong> dominates Endless Mode. Lifesteal becomes mandatory when enemies hit for 200+ damage per attack. Pair Blood with Frost for survivability.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Core Cards:</strong> Crimson Slash x2, Blood Surge, Vampiric Strike, Blizzard, Frozen Armor</li>
          <li><strong>Key Relics:</strong> Vampire Fang, Frost Crystal, Phoenix Feather, Ice Crown</li>
          <li><strong>Character:</strong> Bloodfang or Crimson Lord</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Scaling Strategy</h2>
        <ul class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Floors 1-20:</strong> Build your deck aggressively. Take every card reward. You want a 25-30 card deck by Floor 20.</li>
          <li><strong>Floors 21-30:</strong> Start thinning. Remove weak starter cards at the Forge. Prioritize relic rooms.</li>
          <li><strong>Floors 31-40:</strong> Your deck should be optimized. 18-22 cards. All relics acquired. Focus on survival.</li>
          <li><strong>Floor 41+:</strong> Pure survival. Healing relics matter more than damage. Phoenix Feather is essential.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Key Tips</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>Never skip Merchant on floors 30+ — healing items scale with your max HP</li>
          <li>Deck Thinner relic is S-tier for Endless Mode</li>
          <li>Phoenix Feather revives you ONCE per run — play safe after it triggers</li>
          <li>At Floor 40+, AoE cards outperform single-target because enemies swarm</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
      <a href="/guides/best-builds" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Best Builds</a>
      <a href="/guides/beginners-guide" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Beginner's Guide</a>
      <a href="/guides/relics-guide" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Relics Guide</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
